radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is dilated, fluid-filled, with mildly thickened and hyperemic walls and adjacent stranding compatible with acute uncomplicated appendicitis. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. Liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, and rectum are all within normal limits. No evidence of free fluid in the pelvis.
